5.3 Secondary Organic Aerosol (SOA) Formation
Secondary Organic Aerosol (SOA) forms when VOCs (volatile organic compounds) are oxidised in the
atmosphere by OH•, On, or NOn•, producing semi-volatile organic compounds (SVOCs) that condense onto
particles. SOA can constitute 30–70% of PMn.n in many regions.
