8. Oxygen and Ozone Chemistry
Oxygen and ozone are central to both stratospheric (beneficial) and tropospheric (harmful) chemistry.
Understanding both contexts is essential for UGC NET.
8.1 The Chapman Cycle – Stratospheric Ozone
Sidney Chapman (1930) proposed the natural ozone formation and destruction cycle in the stratosphere. This is
the pure oxygen mechanism – explains the natural On layer without CFCs.
