9. Photochemical Smog
Photochemical smog (Los Angeles-type / oxidising smog) is a complex mixture of pollutants formed by
photochemical reactions of NOx and VOCs in sunlight. It is characterised by high ozone, PAN, and brownish
haze. First observed in Los Angeles in the 1940s; now a problem in all major cities including Delhi, Mumbai.
