10. UGC NET Pattern MCQs with Explanations
Q1. The most abundant gas in the Earth's atmosphere is:
(a) Oxygen (On)
(b) Carbon dioxide (COn)
(c) Nitrogen (Nn)
(d) Argon (Ar)
4 Answer: (c)
Explanation: Nitrogen (Nn) constitutes ~78.09% of dry air by volume. On is 20.95%, Ar is 0.93%, COn is ~0.042%
(421 ppm in 2024). This is a must-know fact for UGC NET.
Q2. PMn.n is more hazardous than PMnn because:
(a) It contains more sulphate
(b) It reaches the alveoli and can enter the bloodstream
(c) It has higher settling velocity
(d) It is primary in origin
4 Answer: (b)
Explanation: PMn.n (< 2.5 μm) is fine enough to penetrate deep into alveolar region of lungs, and ultrafine fraction
can cross into bloodstream. PMnn is filtered by nose/throat. This makes PMn.n far more hazardous for
cardiovascular and respiratory health.
Q3. The "detergent of the atmosphere" is:
(a) Ozone (On)
(b) Hydrogen peroxide (HnOn)
(c) Hydroxyl radical (OH•)
(d) Nitrate radical (NOn•)
4 Answer: (c)
Explanation: OH• (hydroxyl radical) is called the atmosphere's detergent because it oxidises virtually all reduced
trace gases (CHn, CO, VOCs, SOn, NOn). It is the primary daytime oxidant. Global average [OH•] » 10n
molecules/cm³.
Q4. Which reaction initiates the Chapman cycle for stratospheric ozone formation?
(a) On + hn ® On + O(¹D)
(b) On + hn (< 242 nm) ® 2O•
(c) NO + On ® NOn + On
(d) OH• + On ® HOn• + On
4 Answer: (b)
Explanation: The Chapman cycle begins with photodissociation of On by UV-C radiation (< 242 nm) in the upper
stratosphere: On + hn ® 2O•. The O atoms then combine with On to form On. Option (a) is ozone photolysis
(destruction step).
Q5. Peroxyacyl Nitrate (PAN) is significant because:
(a) It is a primary pollutant from vehicle exhausts
(b) It depletes stratospheric ozone
(c) It transports NOx long distances and acts as a phytotoxic eye irritant
(d) It is a major GHG
4 Answer: (c)
