11. Assertion–Reason Questions
Q1. [Assertion–Reason]
Assertion (A): Tropospheric ozone is considered a pollutant while stratospheric ozone is beneficial.
Reason (R): Ozone at all altitudes has the same chemical formula On and identical chemical properties.
(a) Both A and R are true and R is the correct explanation of A (b) Both A and R are true but R is NOT the
correct explanation (c) A is true but R is false (d) A is false but R is true
4 Answer: (b)
Explanation: A is true: tropospheric On damages crops, lungs, and materials; stratospheric On shields UV-B. R is
true (On is On chemically) BUT R is NOT the correct explanation – the difference is due to LOCATION and context,
not chemistry. Select (b).
Q2. [Assertion–Reason]
Assertion (A): Photochemical smog is most severe in the afternoon hours (1–4 PM).
Reason (R): NOn photolysis and VOC oxidation require sunlight, and solar intensity peaks around
midday.
(a) Both A and R are true and R is the correct explanation of A (b) Both A and R are true but R is NOT the
correct explanation (c) A is true but R is false (d) A is false but R is true
4 Answer: (a)
Explanation: Both A and R are correct. Smog chemistry requires UV light (NOn + hn). Peak solar intensity occurs
around noon; smog products (On, PAN) accumulate with a lag of 1–3 hours ® peak at 1–4 PM. R correctly explains
A. Select (a).
Q3. [Assertion–Reason]
Assertion (A): The Montreal Protocol successfully controlled CFC emissions and the ozone hole is
currently showing signs of recovery.
Reason (R): CFCs have very short atmospheric lifetimes (< 1 year) and are quickly removed from the
stratosphere.
(a) Both A and R are true and R is the correct explanation of A (b) Both A and R are true but R is NOT the
correct explanation (c) A is true but R is false (d) A is false but R is true
4 Answer: (c)
Explanation: A is TRUE – the ozone hole is indeed healing (UNEP reports confirm gradual recovery). R is FALSE –
CFCs have atmospheric lifetimes of 45–100 YEARS, allowing them to persist and reach the stratosphere. That's why
recovery takes decades. Select (c).
Q4. [Assertion–Reason]
Assertion (A): Nitrate radical (NOn•) is the dominant nighttime oxidant in the troposphere.
Reason (R): NOn• is rapidly photolysed during daytime by sunlight and therefore only accumulates at
night.
(a) Both A and R are true and R is the correct explanation of A (b) Both A and R are true but R is NOT the
correct explanation (c) A is true but R is false (d) A is false but R is true
4 Answer: (a)
Explanation: Both A and R are true and R correctly explains A. NOn• (formed from NOn+On) is destroyed within
seconds by daytime UV (NOn• + hn ® NOn + O•). At night, with no sunlight, NOn• accumulates and oxidises VOCs,
DMS, and other species. Select (a).
